Brook Trout Abundance and Extreme Flows - Results

Annalise Blum

12/20/2016

Research questions

  1. How do seasonal extremes in climate and streamflow affect brook trout young-of-the-year abundance? To answer look at sign and magnitude of coefficients (effect sizes) in models of abundance
  2. Which seasonal weather metrics (seasinal averages, daily maximum precipitation or daily maximum temperature) and flow metrics (magnitude, duration, or average flow) are most useful in explaining next summer brook trout abundance? To answer look at goodness of fit (lowest AIC, other metrics?) of models with competing metrics
  3. Are there thresholds in these at which there is a clear change in abundance? To answer identify cut-offs with regression trees (other methods? piece-wise) and evaluate whether dummies for above or below threshold
